# Cloudflare Pages — URL rewrites.
#
# /admin/ is a single-page app: one HTML file, JS routes between
# views by reading window.location.pathname. Without this rule,
# navigating directly to /admin/bookings/ would 404 because there's
# no /admin/bookings/index.html on disk. The 200 status code rewrites
# the request to serve /admin/index.html while keeping the visible
# URL in the address bar — the JS then reads pathname and renders
# the right route.
#
# Doesn't affect any other path: Cloudflare Pages tries to find a
# static file first and only falls back to these rules on miss.
# /dashboard/hotel/, /dashboard/login/, /tours/.../, and the rest of
# the static site are unaffected.

/admin/*  /admin/index.html  200
